{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "0383813b6f694d1a", "candidate": {"id": "cand-002", "name": "Tom\u00e1s Nov\u00e1k", "raw_cv": "TOM\u00c1S NOV\u00c1K\ntomas.novak@email.com | Prague \u2192 London, UK\n\nDATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 5 years of experience in financial data infrastructure. Expert in Python, dbt, and cloud data warehouses. EU citizen with indefinite leave to remain in the UK. Available immediately.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nData Engineer \u2014 Revolut, London (2020\u20132024)\n- Built and maintained dbt models powering Revolut's internal financial reporting and regulatory compliance pipelines\n- Led migration from legacy SQL scripts to dbt, creating 80+ tested models in Snowflake\n- Built Airflow DAGs for daily reconciliation and month-end close processes\n- Worked closely with the compliance and finance teams to ensure data accuracy for FCA reporting\n\nData Analyst \u2192 Data Engineer \u2014 Monzo Bank, London (2019\u20132020)\n- Transitioned from analytics to engineering role; built first automated pipeline for chargeback data\n- Maintained BigQuery data models for product analytics\n\nSKILLS\nPython (pandas, pyspark), SQL, dbt, Snowflake, BigQuery, Airflow, Kafka (consumer), Terraform, Docker, GitHub Actions\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Mathematics \u2014 Charles University, Prague (2016\u20132019)\n\nLANGUAGES\nEnglish (fluent), Czech (native), Slovak (fluent)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nEU citizen, UK ILR holder \u2014 no sponsorship required", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer focused on financial data infrastructure and regulatory reporting. Five years in London fintech \u2014 Revolut and Monzo \u2014 building the plumbing that keeps compliance and finance teams happy. I specialise in dbt and Snowflake and have a soft spot for well-tested data models. Czech national with UK ILR, so no visa complications. Looking for a senior data engineering role in a regulated financial environment where data quality genuinely matters. Happy to be in the office \u2014 I find async-only remote cultures don't work well for data engineering.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Thanks for coming in, Tom\u00e1s. Tell me about your experience with dbt at Revolut.\n\nTom\u00e1s: At Revolut I was effectively the dbt lead for the finance data platform. We had over 80 models, all tested with dbt tests and documented. I introduced the staging/intermediate/mart layering pattern there and trained the rest of the team on it. We were on Snowflake the whole time.\n\nInterviewer: And how do you feel about Kafka? We use it heavily for payment events.\n\nTom\u00e1s: I've worked as a consumer \u2014 reading from Kafka topics into our pipelines \u2014 but I haven't architected Kafka infrastructure from scratch. I'm confident I can get up to speed quickly on the producer side, but I want to be honest about the depth of my experience there.\n\nInterviewer: That's fair. What are your thoughts on the office setup? Five days at Canary Wharf.\n\nTom\u00e1s: No issue at all. I live in Wapping, so it's a ten-minute walk. Honestly I've been mostly in the office at Revolut too \u2014 I prefer it for engineering roles.\n\nInterviewer: And your right to work situation?\n\nTom\u00e1s: I have EU settled status with ILR, so I have the right to work indefinitely in the UK. No sponsorship needed.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nTom\u00e1s: I'm at \u00a376,000 currently. I'd be looking for \u00a380\u201385,000 for this move.\n\nInterviewer: Perfect. We'll be in touch shortly.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "pandas", "pyspark", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "BigQuery", "Airflow", "Kafka", "Terraform", "Docker", "GitHub Actions"], "industries": ["fintech", "financial services"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.85, "constraints": [{"id": "ae42af1c", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compe